Jeffrey Y. Grappone of New Hampshire has been nominated for the position of Assistant Secretary of Labor for Public Affairs. He has 15 years of experience in strategic communications, working with Members of Congress, political candidates, and corporate executives. Currently, he serves as a senior communicator at Siemens USA's corporate headquarters in Washington, D.C., where he advises the United States CEO on communications strategy relating to workforce development and apprenticeship programs. Mr. Grappone also leads communications and media relations initiatives for Siemens' energy businesses in the United States. In the past, he served as the communications director and chief spokesman for Senator Kelly Ayotte (NH-R) for four years. He has also worked as a Press Secretary to Senator John E. Sununu (NH-R) and on the legislative staff of Congressman Charles Bass (NH-R). Mr. Grappone is a native of Concord, New Hampshire, and holds a Bachelor of Arts degree in Government from Georgetown University in Washington, D.C.